Page 3
S.B. NO.
C.D. 1
1 preparation of foods that pose a higher risk to public health,
2 as determined by rule.
3 (d) The department of health shall adopt rules pursuant to
4 chapter 91, Hawaii Revised Statutes, necessary for the purposes
5 of this Act.
6 (e) For the purposes of this Act:
7 "Farm kitchen" means a kitchen located on agricultural
8 land, including land zoned for agricultural use or land actively
9 used for agricultural production, in which homemade food
10 products are prepared using ingredients that may include
11 agricultural products grown or raised on the same farm.
12 "Home kitchen" has the same meaning as defined in rules
13 adopted by the department of health.
14 "Homemade food products" has the same meaning as defined in
15 rules adopted by the department of health.
16 SECTION 3. This Act shall take effect upon its approval.
